397
00:25:02,690 --> 00:25:05,360
Wait, are you going to carry all this to your room?

398
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:07,900
Am I supposed to sleep in the bathroom?

399
00:25:08,370 --> 00:25:09,330
Come on.

400
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:12,130
I’m going home today.

401
00:25:12,140 --> 00:25:13,250
It’s a tradition.

402
00:25:13,270 --> 00:25:14,580
I’ll have dinner with my dad.

403
00:25:14,850 --> 00:25:16,850
Wow, what a good kid.

404
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,060
Hey.

405
00:25:18,610 --> 00:25:21,840
When is Yotha’s birthday?

406
00:25:22,490 --> 00:25:23,330
Why do you ask?

407
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:30,380
No reason.

408
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:34,370
I’m just curious.

409
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:37,640
You’re brothers
and you’re close in age.

410
00:25:37,660 --> 00:25:39,550
I just thought that was kind of unusual.

411
00:25:39,570 --> 00:25:40,740
Stop lying.

412
00:25:41,900 --> 00:25:44,520
Fine, I’ll tell you.

413
00:25:44,820 --> 00:25:46,820
Yotha’s birthday is April 8.

414
00:25:47,260 --> 00:25:47,900
Write it down.

415
00:25:50,170 --> 00:25:51,900
Oh, okay.

416
00:25:52,030 --> 00:25:53,900
I’ll already forget it tomorrow.

417
00:25:54,210 --> 00:25:56,420
No one has teased you about it.

418
00:25:57,810 --> 00:25:59,560
I don't think you’ll see him today, though.

419
00:25:59,580 --> 00:26:02,120
He’s having dinner with me, Dad, and Newton.

420
00:26:02,410 --> 00:26:03,880
Oh? Why?

421
00:26:03,910 --> 00:26:04,790
Why do you ask?

422
00:26:04,820 --> 00:26:05,900
Do you want to come with us?

423
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,880
Fine, I don’t want to know anymore.

424
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,900
It’s our tradition.

425
00:26:11,930 --> 00:26:14,030
We have a meal with Dad on our birthday.

426
00:26:14,060 --> 00:26:15,660
