really traumatized us.

566
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:06,010
How?

567
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:14,240
Dad said he’ll never find someone else to replace Mom
because he’s done with love.

568
00:33:15,580 --> 00:33:20,100
He’s scared of hurting someone new
and making them walk away like Mom did.

569
00:33:21,370 --> 00:33:24,290
I play around

570
00:33:25,530 --> 00:33:26,970
but when it starts getting serious with someone,

571
00:33:28,060 --> 00:33:30,560
I always get scared.

572
00:33:32,060 --> 00:33:33,060
And look at Fai.

573
00:33:33,790 --> 00:33:37,110
He’s nice to everyone
because he’s scared people won’t love him

574
00:33:37,570 --> 00:33:40,630
but he actually doesn't even know how to love.

575
00:33:42,300 --> 00:33:43,090
What about me?

576
00:33:43,420 --> 00:33:46,330
You’re the only brave one.

577
00:33:46,580 --> 00:33:48,110
You took a chance with Warich

578
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:50,430
but in the end,

579
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:53,400
you got hurt.

580
00:33:57,580 --> 00:33:59,500
What do you think I should do now?

581
00:34:00,430 --> 00:34:02,430
Right now, Gun is taking a risk with you.

582
00:34:03,260 --> 00:34:04,180
I’ll only take that risk

583
00:34:05,900 --> 00:34:07,900
if I’m sure it’s love.

584
00:34:08,490 --> 00:34:10,100
Isn’t that too selfish?

585
00:34:13,340 --> 00:34:14,760
I don’t want to end up like Dad,

586
00:34:17,420 --> 00:34:18,840
watching Mom leave with someone else.

587
00:34:21,540 --> 00:34:23,110
I don’t want Gun to get hurt like I did

588
00:34:26,220 --> 00:34:28,680
when Warich said what we had wasn’t love.

589
00:34:39,840 --> 00:34:40,500
Hi, Mom.

590
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:41,490
What’s up, son?

591
00:34:41,850 --> 00:34:43,000
I’m sleeping alone tonight.

592
00:34:43,740 --> 00:34:45,080
My friend went home.

593
00:34:45,100 --> 00:34:46,480
You’re allowed to go home?

594
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:48,660
I thought it was against the dorm rules.

595
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:51,080
You can come home and visit me then.

596
00:34:52,130 --> 00:34:54,320
My friend just doesn’t care about the rules.

597
00:34:54,340 --> 00:34:55,890
He’s a bad boy.

598
00:34:55,900 --> 00:34:56,630
Really?

599
00:34:56,660 --> 00:34:58,110
I miss you.

600
00:34:58,450 --> 00:35:00,450
Come visit me on some weekends.

601
00:35:04,770 --> 00:35:05,690
Hey, Mom.

602
00:35:06,330 --> 00:35:08,160
Can I bring my friend to visit?

603
00:35:08,170 --> 00:35:09,200
Friend or partner?

604
00:35:09,220 --> 00:35:10,440
Friend.

605
00:35:10,460 --> 00:35:12,400
Either way, you can bring them.

606
00:35:12,940 --> 00:35:16,310
But you have to let me know in advance
so I can get ready.

607
00:35:17,110 --> 00:35:20,010
How about next weekend?

608
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:20,650
Okay.

609
00:35:20,910 --> 00:35:22,290
I’ll be waiting.

610
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:24,170
I miss you so much.

611
00:35:24,180 --> 00:35:25,880
I miss you too.

612
00:35:49,290 --> 00:35:51,810
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
ARE YOU FREE TO TALK?

613
00:35:53,340 --> 00:35:54,411
Tell me honestly,

614
00:35:55,640 --> 00:35:57,011
have you ever really loved me?

615
00:35:59,114 --> 00:36:03,080
I’m sorry that I’m only sure about this now.

616
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:08,268
Then remember

617
00:36:08,291 --> 00:36:11,617
that your uncertainty hurt me so much.

618
00:36:13,340 --> 00:36:14,228
Yotha.

619
00:36:18,285 --> 00:36:19,251
Thank you

620
00:36:20,868 --> 00:36:22,860
for breaking another world of mine.

621
00:36:29,410 --> 00:36:30,497
Can I stay with you tonight?

622
00:36:36,690 --> 00:36:39,337
It’s been so long since I’ve slept in a dark room like this.

623
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,525
I’m not really used to it anymore.

624
00:36:42,010 --> 00:36:43,885
Why are you sleeping here tonight?

625
00:36:44,470 --> 00:36:45,028
Why?

626
00:36:45,720 --> 00:36:48,457
Can’t I stay the night with my dear brother?

627
00:36:51,340 --> 00:36:55,434
Alright, I just wanted to apologize
for meddling in your business with Gun.

628
00:36:55,890 --> 00:36:57,520
Once we go back to the dorm, I’ll switch rooms back.

629
00:36:58,090 --> 00:36:59,502
It’s better for him to stay with you.

630
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:01,102
Why?

631
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:02,748
What’s wrong?

632
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:04,314
I’m too lazy to explain right now.

633
00:37:04,331 --> 00:37:05,131
I’m sleepy.

634
00:37:06,170 --> 00:37:09,765
Yo, what’s going on between you and Gun?

635
00:37:11,060 --> 00:37:12,491
I’m figuring it out.

636
00:37:14,310 --> 00:37:15,240
What do you mean?

637
00:37:18,010 --> 00:37:20,337
In the meantime, please take care of him.

638
00:37:36,940 --> 00:37:37,605
Yotha.

639
00:37:50,970 --> 00:37:52,017
Aren’t you going to class?

640
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:53,605
I’m about to.

641
00:37:54,140 --> 00:37:55,605
How was dinner with your family last night?

642
00:37:56,822 --> 00:37:58,582
Isn’t that too selfish?

643
00:38:03,108 --> 00:38:05,897
You have the right to protect your feelings, Yotha,

644
00:38:07,560 --> 00:38:10,165
but think carefully before you do anything.

645
00:38:11,410 --> 00:38:13,908
And please protect the feelings
of the one by your side, too.

646
00:38:21,490 --> 00:38:23,114
Same as usual.

647
00:38:23,580 --> 00:38:25,897
Faifa said you guys drank until late.

648
00:38:26,222 --> 00:38:27,697
No wonder you didn’t reply to my text.

649
00:38:29,580 --> 00:38:32,405
I didn’t see it.

650
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:33,777
Is something the matter?

651
00:38:35,100 --> 00:38:36,451
Are you free next weekend?

652
00:38:37,257 --> 00:38:39,250
I’ll take you to my house like I promised.

653
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:40,937
Your house?

654
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:41,908
Yeah.

655
00:38:42,170 --> 00:38:43,194
In Chantaburi.

656
00:38:43,702 --> 00:38:46,542
I already told my mom I’m bringing my friend.

657
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:48,165
She’s okay with it

658
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:50,600
and will prepare delicious food for us.

659
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:54,542
I’m busy.

660
00:38:55,410 --> 00:38:56,062
Oh?

661
00:38:57,497 --> 00:38:58,222
Really?

662
00:39:02,430 --> 00:39:03,222
I’m sorry.

663
00:39:03,810 --> 00:39:04,982
I forgot to ask you first.

664
00:39:06,794 --> 00:39:07,640
I’m sorry.

665
00:39:09,570 --> 00:39:10,485
No worries.

666
00:39:11,325 --> 00:39:13,320
I’ll go alone this time.

667
00:39:13,577 --> 00:39:15,320
Next time, we can go together.

668
00:39:15,908 --> 00:39:16,908
Let’s hurry to class.

669
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:19,314
I need to check my attendance.

670
00:39:25,342 --> 00:39:26,702
What can I get for you?

671
00:39:31,460 --> 00:39:32,994
Hey!

672
00:39:33,005 --> 00:39:33,451
Oh.

673
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:36,251
Can I get rice noodles?

674
00:39:36,274 --> 00:39:38,171
I sell rice and curry.

675
00:39:39,330 --> 00:39:39,885
Oh.

676
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:41,937
Then I'll have minced pork with basil.

677
00:39:41,954 --> 00:39:42,702
Sure.

678
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:43,165
Just that.

679
00:39:43,188 --> 00:39:43,714
Okay.

680
00:39:45,890 --> 00:39:47,154
Here you go.

681
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:49,114
40 baht, please.

682
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:57,531
Gun.

683
00:39:59,940 --> 00:40:01,262
Are you not feeling well?

684
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:07,085
I probably have a bit of a headache.

685
00:40:07,330 --> 00:40:09,662
Do you, or do you probably have a headache?

686
00:40:09,680 --> 00:40:10,525
I do, a bit.

687
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:12,628
Then after you’re done eating,

688
00:40:12,651 --> 00:40:14,620
go buy some medicine before you go to class, okay?

689
00:40:15,090 --> 00:40:16,251
Hey, Ears.

690
00:40:16,274 --> 00:40:18,800
You can tell us anything.

691
00:40:19,370 --> 00:40:20,451
Look.

692
00:40:23,217 --> 00:40:24,897
I really have a headache.

693
00:40:25,590 --> 00:40:27,200
I’m probably about to get sick.

694
00:40:28,090 --> 00:40:30,388
Why? Can’t I feel a bit down?

695
00:40:30,417 --> 00:40:34,640
You’re usually the sunshine of this world.

696
00:40:34,670 --> 00:40:37,897
When you’re down, it’s kinda weird.

697
00:40:40,820 --> 00:40:42,422
If the answer is no,

698
00:40:44,220 --> 00:40:45,205
will you be sad?

699
00:40:46,300 --> 00:40:46,960
No,

700
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:49,897
because I’m the sunshine of this world.

701
00:40:53,890 --> 00:40:56,302
Alright, let me get sick for just a little while.

702
00:40:56,710 --> 00:40:57,977
I’ll be your sunshine again soon.

703
00:40:57,994 --> 00:40:59,857
Don’t be annoyed with me later.

704
00:41:02,102 --> 00:41:03,897
I’d rather be annoyed than worried about you.

705
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:06,600
That’s so touching

706
00:41:06,628 --> 00:41:07,977
I could cry.

707
00:41:07,994 --> 00:41:09,062
What’s wrong with you?

708
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:11,108
Hey!

709
00:41:13,950 --> 00:41:15,171
Chew before you speak!

710
00:41:15,188 --> 00:41:16,405
You slapped him so hard.

711
00:41:16,422 --> 00:41:17,891
Book, give me your fried rice.

712
00:41:18,548 --> 00:41:19,851
Then get my fried rice,

713
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:21,657
but give me your pork!

714
00:41:33,411 --> 00:41:34,211
Go ahead.

715
00:41:34,990 --> 00:41:36,422
Let me drink some water first.

716
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:39,834
I’m going to faint.

717
00:41:40,820 --> 00:41:41,862
You’re almost there, Fai.

718
00:41:42,460 --> 00:41:43,348
Almost there.

719
00:41:43,668 --> 00:41:44,508
Almost there.

720
00:41:47,140 --> 00:41:47,714
It’s closed.

721
00:41:48,217 --> 00:41:49,177
Closed.

722
00:41:50,740 --> 00:41:52,211
The drink shop is closed.

723
00:41:52,890 --> 00:41:54,131
I can’t take it anymore.

724
00:41:55,885 --> 00:41:56,897
I need some water right now.

725
00:41:56,902 --> 00:41:58,234
Are you okay?

726
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:03,114
Water.

727
00:42:03,620 --> 00:42:04,377
Water.

728
00:42:05,410 --> 00:42:06,714
I’m so thirsty.

729
00:42:06,737 --> 00:42:08,211
I drank a bit already.

730
00:42:08,234 --> 00:42:09,565
You don’t need to use the straw.

731
00:42:15,680 --> 00:42:16,805
Drink slowly.

732
00:42:17,100 --> 00:42:18,108
You don’t want to choke.

733
00:42:20,050 --> 00:42:24,194
If I had to choose between choking to death

734
00:42:24,640 --> 00:42:26,660
and dehydrating to death,
I’d rather choke than not drink water.

735
00:42:26,668 --> 00:42:27,588
You’re weird.

736
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:29,080
How?

737
00:42:29,780 --> 00:42:31,457
You came to work out.

738
00:42:31,474 --> 00:42:33,234
Why didn’t you bring water?

739
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:34,577
It’s important.

740
00:42:35,190 --> 00:42:36,497
I brought it,

741
00:42:36,508 --> 00:42:37,771
but I already gave it to someone else.

742
00:42:37,794 --> 00:42:38,971
That doesn’t count.

743
00:42:40,310 --> 00:42:41,765
You’re such a nag, water boy.

744
00:42:41,782 --> 00:42:42,740
My name is not Water.

745
00:42:42,760 --> 00:42:43,977
Your name is Wine.

746
00:42:43,994 --> 00:42:45,280
I know.

747
00:42:45,314 --> 00:42:46,805
I’m just kidding.

748
00:42:48,050 --> 00:42:49,691
What are you doing here?

749
00:42:50,040 --> 00:42:50,805
Tutoring class?

750
00:42:51,190 --> 00:42:51,697
Yes.

751
00:42:52,060 --> 00:42:53,765
But I’m done and about to go home.

752
00:42:55,430 --> 00:42:57,017
Do you want me to tutor you?

753
00:42:57,017 --> 00:42:59,010
Despite how I look, I’m a bright student.

754
00:43:00,250 --> 00:43:00,971
It’s okay.

755
00:43:01,011 --> 00:43:02,102
My mom already paid for my classes.

756
00:43:04,010 --> 00:43:05,617
Thank you, by the way.

757
00:43:05,970 --> 00:43:09,411
If it wasn’t for you, I’d have died back there.

758
00:43:10,970 --> 00:43:12,400
I should go.

759
00:43:12,422 --> 00:43:12,982
Hey.

760
00:43:13,560 --> 00:43:14,314
Have you eaten?

761
00:43:16,628 --> 00:43:19,582
If not, can I treat you to a meal
as a thank you for the water?

762
00:43:19,820 --> 00:43:20,800
Don’t worry about it.

763
00:43:21,420 --> 00:43:22,085
Come on.

764
00:43:22,114 --> 00:43:24,851
If I get accepted to this uni,

765
00:43:25,462 --> 00:43:27,460
you can treat me then.

766
00:43:30,645 --> 00:43:31,222
Fine.

767
00:43:36,810 --> 00:43:38,382
I owe you two things now.

768
00:43:38,860 --> 00:43:39,760
Don’t forget.

769
00:43:53,965 --> 00:43:54,468
Oh.

770
00:43:58,100 --> 00:43:58,977
You’re back.

771
00:44:00,040 --> 00:44:00,605
Mm.

772
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:04,114
Have you eaten?

773
00:44:04,930 --> 00:44:05,857
Yes.

774
00:44:09,300 --> 00:44:09,891
Oh.

775
00:44:10,620 --> 00:44:12,102
Do you want to go upstairs now?

776
00:44:12,131 --> 00:44:13,097
We can go together.

777
00:44:31,314 --> 00:44:33,310
Is Fai back?

778
00:44:34,970 --> 00:44:35,902
Not yet.

779
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:38,445
He said he had practice for the contest.

780
00:44:42,650 --> 00:44:43,702
You should go inside.

781
00:44:44,360 --> 00:44:45,765
Get a lot of rest.

782
00:44:54,170 --> 00:44:55,022
Yotha.

783
00:44:57,290 --> 00:44:57,880
Hmm?

784
00:44:59,140 --> 00:45:00,411
Tonight…

785
00:45:09,160 --> 00:45:10,222
Nothing.

786
00:45:10,690 --> 00:45:12,388
You should go take a shower and sleep.

787
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:16,240
I’ll come down to stay the night with you.

788
00:46:03,970 --> 00:46:06,040
The practice for the contest is something else.

789
00:46:06,660 --> 00:46:08,285
It’s more tiring than reserve officer training.

790
00:46:13,900 --> 00:46:14,657
Puppy,

791
00:46:16,605 --> 00:46:17,582
what’s wrong?

792
00:46:21,485 --> 00:46:22,731
I’m just being silly.

793
00:46:23,880 --> 00:46:25,268
I said I could wait,

794
00:46:26,550 --> 00:46:27,834
but I’m scared of the answer.

795
00:46:30,880 --> 00:46:32,331
What’s wrong? Tell me.

796
00:46:36,560 --> 00:46:38,228
Yotha said he’s not sure

797
00:46:39,540 --> 00:46:41,297
if what we’ve had is love.

798
00:46:42,170 --> 00:46:43,382
I said I could wait.

799
00:46:44,860 --> 00:46:46,297
That I’d wait no matter how long it takes.

800
00:46:47,885 --> 00:46:50,788
Did he tell you how long you have to wait?

801
00:46:51,890 --> 00:46:53,120
It could be a day,

802
00:46:54,017 --> 00:46:54,960
a month,

803
00:46:57,074 --> 00:46:58,297
or a year.

804
00:46:59,890 --> 00:47:01,285
He said that?

805
00:47:06,210 --> 00:47:07,868
But he’s not wrong.

806
00:47:09,270 --> 00:47:12,302
It’s good that he’s honest with me.

807
00:47:13,140 --> 00:47:14,011
It’s good,

808
00:47:14,662 --> 00:47:16,931
but you’re feeling bad?

809
00:47:20,220 --> 00:47:21,862
I’m just scared, Faifa.

810
00:47:23,780 --> 00:47:24,554
What are you scared of?

811
00:47:26,960 --> 00:47:28,634
I’m scared that it’s not love.

812
00:47:32,220 --> 00:47:35,125
I’m scared that he doesn’t love me.

813
00:47:39,730 --> 00:47:40,691
Oh, puppy.

814
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:45,548
Yotha is not wrong for taking his time

815
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:47,440
and you’re not wrong for waiting,

816
00:47:48,190 --> 00:47:50,462
but it’s also not wrong to ask while waiting.

817
00:47:52,868 --> 00:47:54,285
Can I ask him?

818
00:47:55,160 --> 00:47:56,474
Of course, you can.

819
00:47:59,070 --> 00:48:01,422
At least you’ll make him realize

820
00:48:03,405 --> 00:48:05,400
that you’re waiting for his answer.

821
00:48:13,130 --> 00:48:14,154
Don’t cry.

822
00:48:15,420 --> 00:48:16,291
Don’t cry.

823
00:48:38,502 --> 00:48:39,948
Don’t have nightmares, Beagle.

824
00:48:57,690 --> 00:48:58,405
That sounds delicious!

825
00:48:58,422 --> 00:49:00,594
It’s limited, you know?

826
00:49:00,622 --> 00:49:02,051
They only sell 50 per day.

827
00:49:02,500 --> 00:49:03,571
Let’s go.

828
00:49:10,380 --> 00:49:11,074
Hey.

829
00:49:12,600 --> 00:49:14,497
It seemed like you were having a nightmare last night

830
00:49:14,514 --> 00:49:15,885
and you were crying,

831
00:49:16,450 --> 00:49:17,617
even though the lights were on.

832
00:49:19,070 --> 00:49:20,234
I didn’t know that.

833
00:49:21,470 --> 00:49:23,182
Do you remember what you dreamed about?

834
00:49:26,645 --> 00:49:27,582
Yotha.

835
00:49:29,060 --> 00:49:30,371
Do you…

836
00:49:33,880 --> 00:49:35,194
have the answer for me yet?

837
00:49:46,891 --> 00:49:47,880
I’m sorry.

838
00:49:49,040 --> 00:49:50,000
It’s okay.

839
00:49:50,750 --> 00:49:52,400
I said I could wait,

840
00:49:54,330 --> 00:49:56,388
but I pressured you for an answer.

841
00:49:57,960 --> 00:49:59,154
I should be the one to apologize.

842
00:49:59,530 --> 00:50:03,422
If someone makes you love them more than me,

843
00:50:09,097 --> 00:50:10,388
you’re free to go.

844
00:50:21,740 --> 00:50:22,611
I gotta go.

845
00:52:02,731 --> 00:52:07,897
♪ No worries, give me a chance to try ♪

846
00:52:12,980 --> 00:52:15,982
♪ I’ll open up your heart to a new light inside ♪

847
00:52:16,017 --> 00:52:23,034
♪ True love is real, though you’re not into ♪

848
00:52:23,051 --> 00:52:27,868
♪ I’m reaching for you, believe me, won’t you? ♪

849
00:52:56,794 --> 00:52:58,790
I’ll go smoke outside.

850
00:53:00,010 --> 00:53:00,520
Okay.

851
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:19,600
I got back with Klao.

852
00:53:21,420 --> 00:53:21,971
Yeah.

853
00:53:22,500 --> 00:53:23,400
I’m happy for you.

854
00:53:27,110 --> 00:53:28,228
What’s wrong?

855
00:53:28,245 --> 00:53:29,480
Why are you sitting here alone?

856
00:53:57,940 --> 00:53:58,925
Are you done smoking?

857
00:54:00,331 --> 00:54:02,330
No, I just didn’t want you to smell it.

858
00:54:04,840 --> 00:54:06,245
Let’s go inside.

859
00:54:07,310 --> 00:54:08,491
Are you done talking to him?

860
00:54:10,490 --> 00:54:11,680
Yotha already left.

861
00:54:14,220 --> 00:54:17,897
Doesn’t he usually get beaten up before leaving?

862
00:54:35,080 --> 00:54:36,331
You really reek of cigarettes.

863
00:54:42,400 --> 00:54:43,491
You started this.

864
00:55:08,148 --> 00:55:09,000
Why are you smiling?

865
00:55:34,330 --> 00:55:35,537
Are you tired tonight?

866
00:55:37,890 --> 00:55:39,045
If I say I’m tired,

867
00:55:40,160 --> 00:55:41,297
will you let me sleep?

868
00:55:42,110 --> 00:55:43,211
I’ll let you

869
00:55:44,970 --> 00:55:46,102
lie still.

870
00:56:42,560 --> 00:56:43,297
You smell bad.

871
00:56:57,250 --> 00:56:58,182
And taste bitter.

872
00:57:01,250 --> 00:57:03,331
When will you let me take a shower then?

873
00:57:07,268 --> 00:57:08,874
Did I say I don’t like it?

874
00:57:22,760 --> 00:57:25,388
Do you give him these eyes when you talk to him?

875
00:57:25,760 --> 00:57:27,131
